qas.question: The Kyoto Protocol is associated with what treaty?

answers.text: United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change

qas.question: The United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change was supplemented by what protocol?
The United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change established a framework for the development of what?
While the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change established a framework for developing greenhouse gas emission limits, the Kyoto Protocol contained what?

answers.text: the specific provisions and regulations later agreed upon

qas.question: The agreement that contained specific provisions related to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change is an example of what agreement that supplements a treaty?

context: Some examples: the <a0_0>United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change<a0_0/> (UNFCCC) established a framework for the development of <a2_0>binding greenhouse gas emission limits<a2_0/>, while <a1_0>the Kyoto <a4_0>Protocol<a4_0/><a1_0/> contained <a3_0>the specific provisions and regulations later agreed upon<a3_0/>.
